The third episode of Our Two Kobo, ‘The State of the Nation’, centres on the many challenges faced by Nigerians. In this episode, Jam Jam and The Honourable talk about the challenges, which range from insecurity to increasing food prices, poverty and unemployment. They reminisce about the times things appeared to have been easier for Nigerians, and what a change in government in 2023 may mean for the nation. They also discuss the attack on St. Francis Catholic Church in Owo, Ondo state, where several persons were killed and others injured by gunmen. Click on the link below to listen to this episode on Anchor FM, Spotify and Google podcast.  In case you missed our first two episodes, you can listen here. Please, let us know how we can serve you better. Send us your recommendations, complaints, and suggestions to thecablepodcast@gmail.com.